title: The Right calls a vote of no confidence against the current government!
subtitle: We have angered our coalition partners too much...
new-page: true
on-arrival: tried_supporting_cp = 0
view-if: ccf_in_government = 1 and ((in_grand_coalition = 1 or in_popular_front = 1 or in_minority_government = 1) and coalition_dissent >= 3) or (in_weimar_coalition = 1 and coalition_dissent >= 4) and ccf_r < 50 and not constructive_vonc
tags: event
go-to: vonc_menu

# Options: spend relations to reduce coalition_dissent, ask for cp to abstain
# (lmao CP toleration arc...)

= Vote of No Confidence

[? if in_grand_coalition : The CPC ?][? if in_weimar_coalition or in_popular_front or in_minority_government: The RPC Party ?] has called for a vote of no confidence against us, due to our various policies and disagreements. If this succeeds, there will be an election in a few months.

@vonc_menu

- @try_assuage: Try to assuage our partners.
- @support_cp: Could we get the CP to abstain?
- @let_it_happen: Let the vote happen.

@try_assuage

How do we assuage our partners?

- @give_up_prussia: Give up on leadership of Prussia.
- @austerity: Enact a massive austerity plan.
- @resources: Use our resources to reduce dissent within the coalition.
- @support_cp: Could we get the CP to abstain?
- @let_it_happen: Never mind. Let the vote happen.

@give_up_prussia
view-if: ccf_prussia == 1
on-arrival: coalition_dissent = 0; ccf_prussia = 0; prussian_government = "I"; reformist_dissent += 10; centrist_dissent += 10; labor_dissent += 10; left_dissent += 5; workers_ccf -= 5; rural_ccf -= 5; 

Fine. We no longer control the government of Prussia. The vote has been called off.

@austerity
view-if: welfare >= 0 and not secularized
on-arrival: coalition_dissent = 0; workers_ccf -= 10; unemployed_ccf -= 10; workers_cp += 7; workers_nsdap += 3; unemployed_cp += 5; unemployed_nsdap += 5; left_dissent += 15; center_dissent += 10; labor_dissent += 15; reformist_dissent += 5; welfare -= 2; budget += 1; unemployed += 3; cp_coalition_dissent += 1; cp_relation -= 10 if in_popular_front

Fine. We enacted a massive austerity program to cut welfare, in order to maintain the stability of our coalition. The vote has been called off.

@resources
view-if: secularized = 0
choose-if: resources >= 3
unavailable-subtitle: We do not have enough resources.
subtitle: -3 resources
on-arrival: resources -= 3; coalition_dissent -= 1;

By transferring resources to our coalition partners, we can reduce their dissent against our policies. This is a crude, but effective solution.

@support_cp
choose-if: (in_grand_coalition and communist_coalition >= 3 and cp_relation >= 50 and cp_r >= cpc_r) or (in_weimar_coalition and cp_relation >= 50 and cp_r >= rpc_r and communist_coalition >= 3)
view-if: tried_supporting_cp = 0
on-arrival: tried_supporting_cp = 1
unavailable-subtitle: [? if communist_coalition < 3 : The CP won't take part in parliamentary government. ?] [? if cp_relation < 50 : The CP is not friendly enough with us. ?] [? if (in_grand_coalition and cp_r < cpc_r) or (in_weimar_coalition and cp_r < rpc_r): The CP does not have enough votes. ?] [? if in_popular_front : We are already in a Popular Front with the CP. ?]

If the Communists abstain, then we essentially can maintain a minority government[? if monarch=="George V":, although it would be very difficult to make policy without the support of Monarch George V, which we do not have ?]. If this happens, then we will own a massive debt to the CP. This could lead to broader cooperation in the future, for better or for worse.

- @support_cp_2: Persuade the CP to "tolerate" us?
- @let_it_happen: Never mind. Let the vote happen.

@support_cp_2
on-arrival: communist_coalition += 1; workers_cp += 3; cp_relation += 5
go-to: support_cp_weimar if in_weimar_coalition; support_cp_grand if in_grand_coalition

